§BIt is 101 AUC (653BC) , Pharaoh Psamtik I has just reunited the Twin Kingdoms of Egypt and thrown out the Assyrian conquerers... Egypt is again united under a Pharaoh... will the Saite dynasty be able to consolidate power and stabilize the land of the double crowns? The Assyrian Empire has been bested by it's former client kingdom, will the High King Ashurbanipal strike back? or has a new dawn come? signifying to the other client kingdoms that Assyria's grip may be slipping.... Choose your role in these turbulent times and play as either a humble nobleman, prince, or a King§!

column2: The Early form of the Republic, lasting until about the reign of Augustus which ushered in the Principate or Imperial system.

The Ancient beliefs of Mesopotamia continued on in many forms until the arrival of Christianity in Mesopotamia proper during the common era. The many deities and originally independant city-states led to a Henotheistic belief system in which many gods were recognized and worshipped. The most prominent of the Akkadian/Mesopotamian deities were Marduk, Ishtar, Sîn, Samash, and Anu.

The God Armazi is believed to be a fusion of the ancient Hittite & Luwian beliefs, and the worship of Ahura Mazda and the local deity Arma. Influences of Ahura Mazda would have carried over from the Avestan faiths, while the local Anatolian deity, Arma was then combined and over time a Pantheon of Urartian deities developed.

East African religion is a blanket term for the diverse pagan beliefs of the tribes of North-East Africa. Ancestor worship, animism and totemistic shamanism dominate, but there also various numbers of gods & spirits. Defining features in-game:
§Y*§! Can declare Subjugation Wars against all other pagans
§Y*§! Rulers are limited to Gavelkind Succession
§Y*§! Rulers cannot declare Holy Wars
§Y*§! Inferior at conversion and vulnerable to non-pagan missionaries
§Y*§! Defensive bonuses in West African Pagan counties
§Y*§!

La religion ouest-africaine est un terme qui recouvre les diverses croyances païennes des tribus de l'Afrique de l'Ouest sub-saharienne. Le culte des ancêtres, l'animisme et le chamanisme totémique y dominent, mais on y trouve aussi divers panthéons. Dans le jeu :
§Y*§! Peuvent piller les voisins pour obtenir un butin
§Y*§! Les non-païens qui ont peu de moyens techniques ont une très basse limite de stock dans les comtés païens
§Y*§! Peuvent déclarer des guerres d'assujettissement à tous les autres païens 
§Y*§! Les dirigeants n'ont accès qu'à la succession Gavelkind
§Y*§! Les dirigeants ne peuvent déclarer de guerres saintes
§Y*§! Inférieurs en conversion et vulnérables aux missionnaires non-païens
§Y*§! Bonus défensifs pour les comtés ouest-africains païens
§Y*§! La foi païenne ouest-africaine peut être réformée

Westafrikanische Religion ist ein Oberbegriff für die vielfältigen, heidnischen Glaubensvorstellungen der westafrikanischen Völker südlich der Sahara. Vorfahrenverehrung, Animismus und Schamanismus sind vorherrschend, aber es gibt auch mehrere Götterpantheone. Bestimmende Merkmale im Spiel: 
§Y*§!Kann Nachbarn überfallen und plündern
§Y*§! Nicht-Heiden haben eine sehr geringere Maximal-Versorgung in heidnischen Regionen
§Y*§!Kann Unterwerfungskriege gegen alle anderen Heiden ausrufen

§Y*§!Herrscher können keine Heiligen Kriege ausrufen

§Y*§!Verteidigungsboni in heidnischen westafrikanischen Regionen
§Y*§!Das westafrikanische Heidentum kann reformiert werden

column2: The Proxenos is appointed with the responsibility of hosting foreign Dignitaries and Ambassadors during their visits at the court. It is a prestigious position and best reserved for those with an open mind and cordial mannerisms.

The Kushite faith is very similar to the Egyptian faith and has been heavily influenced by it for hundreds of years, which has resulted in a fusion of the southern Kushite peoples beliefs and their northern Egyptian neighbors. Deities worshipped include Amon, Amesemi, and Apedemak. Defining features in-game:
§Y*§! There is no one religious figurehead for the faith.
§Y*§! Rulers cannot declare Holy Wars
§Y*§! Can declare Subjugation Wars against all other pagans

The Phoenician Faith is a polytheistic faith which is derived from the early faiths of the Levant. Many gods and goddesses where worshipped in the Pantheon of deities and the customs varied from place to place but were uniform in their establishment of many deities.

column2: This character has devoted themselves to the Sumerian deity Ishtar, who was also known as Inanna in Sumerian sources. Worship of her dates back to the Epic of Gilgamesh and her father is the Nanna, the Mesopotamian Moon diety.

This character is a devotee of the Assyrian head god Ashur, and does so in a manner which excludes the remaining pantheon of Mesopotamian deities. Ashur began as a local deity who rose to prominence as the head of the Assyrian Pantheon following the rise of their empire, records indicate worship of him goes back as far as 2045 BC.

Ardys II was the son of the infamous usurper Gyges of Lydia, He is regarded as the twenty-seventh King of Lydia. Most of his reign so far has been occupied with resisting the Cimmerian invasions from Iberia, He is also known for his campaigns against the greeks of Miletus and Priene. The next few years are an important time for Ardys as he must strive to maintain Lydia's borders against foreign invaders and the ever-restless Phrygians and Lycians within his own borders.

A fictional leader of the Etruscan League. The Etruscans are in a precarious position. In the south-east the latin states are growing in power and ambition. To the north the Alpine and Gallic tribes are a constant threat as they raid ever southwards and seek new lands. The League itself is weakened by internal conflicts and jealous neighbors. Shall you attempt to strengthen your league with alliances amongst the neighboring city-states or centralize power in Tarchna? Focus upon the wrong threat and the League could be splint asunder. Italy's fate awaits your decision.

The Last Nubian/Kushite King of Egypt, Tantamani is the nephew of Taharqa and the Son of the great Shabaka. He temporarily ruled all of Egypt after defeating and killing the Assyrian puppet-Pharaoh Necho I, but  Assyrian forces soon returned to Egypt, defeated Tantamani's army, and expelled him from Egypt. Now another Egyptian, Psamtik I the son of Necho, sits and wears the double crown...it is yours by birthright!

The son of Urtaku and recently restored to the throne after the death of the Usurper Te-Umman at the hands of the Assyrians, Ummanigash and his brother Tammaritu (reigning at Hidali near Susa) attempt to reorganize the failing Elamite state after several failed wars with the Assyrians. To further complicate matters, Median power to the north and the roaming Scythians threaten their independence and wellbeing. Recent events in Media and the nearby mountainous region have led the Persian peoples to migrate to Anshan, further destabilizing your borders and raising another dissenting voice within the already-weakened Elamite Kingdom

Similar to tribal government form but with a stronger centralized ruling class of noblemen or warlords, the people also primarly live in large fortified hill-forts (Called Oppidums in Europe) and are quite more technologically "advanced" compared to the other tribal governments.
Submit a portion of your wealth as an offering to the gods in order to request blessings and good omens from them
This character, though not a believer in the Semitic gods, has a special sympathy and understanding for the Semitic beliefs and its practitioners.
column3: Ce personnage, bien qu'il ne soit pas zoroastrien, montre une certaine tolérance et une compréhension relative du zoroastrisme et de ses pratiquants.

column2: Ashurism is the Assyrian faith which is derived from ancient Mesopotamian religions. It was centered around the Assyrian king. However, kingship at the time was linked very closely with the idea of divine mandate. The Assyrian king, whilst not being a god himself, was acknowledged as the chief servant of the chief god, Ashur. In this manner, the king's authority was seen as absolute so long as the high priest reassured the peoples that the gods, or in the case of the henotheistic Assyrians, the God Ashur, was pleased with the current ruler.

The Title of Grand Vizier demands respect within the royal court and indicates a close relationship and trust with the ruler, The Grand Vizier is often tasked as an Envoy or works directly on behalf of their liege.

The Babylonian faith tends to lean towards monotheism as all deities are seen to be subservient to the great deity of Babylon, Merodach. The story of creation is influenced by an "Astral" Aspect, the presence of some form of heaven. The Babylonians revere their ancesters, and have great respect for their King. Defining features in-game:
§Y*§! The King can declare holy wars
§Y*§! Rulers are permitted & expected to have several concubines
§Y*§! Temples may be held by rulers
The §Y$JOB$§! is the councillor in charge of the military. When the ruler cannot or will not command armies, the §Y$JOB$§! will do it.

Notable deities include El, Melqart, Ba'al Hammon and Attar. Defining features in-game:\n§Y*§! There is no central leadership or head of the faith\n§Y*§! There are no Holy Wars

The faiths of the Arabs are mostly polytheistic, being centered on deities such as Hubal, Wadd, and Manat. They practise animist traditions such as the worship of sacred groves and unique meteorite worship, and a pantheon of gods derived mainly from western Semitic sources.Defining features in-game:
§Y*§! Can raid neighbors for loot
§Y*§! Can declare Subjugation Wars against all other pagans
§Y*§! Rulers cannot declare Holy Wars
§Y*§! Inferior at conversion and vulnerable to non-pagan missionaries
§Y*§! Rulers lose Prestige if at peace for too long

The Moabite faith is a Semitic and Babylonian-influenced faith which is polytheistic. The most highly revered god was Chemosh, other deities include Ashtar-Chemosh and Nebo. In times of dire need, the followers of Chemosh believe that human sacrifice would aid in their prayers being heard by the deity. Defining features in-game:
§Y*§! There is no central leadership or head of the faith
§Y*§! There are no Holy Wars
§Y*§! Human Sacrifices are practiced
this person is recognized as the High Priest of the Babylonian Faith and a very holy person in the eyes of the gods

A Semitic religion with influences from Phoenician & Canaanite deities and traditions. Most believers are polytheistic, but there are a few monolatristic as well. Notable deities include El, Melqart, Ba'al Hammon and Attar. Defining features in-game:\n§Y*§! There is no central leadership or head of the faith\n§Y*§! There are no Holy Wars

The Scythians had a pantheon of seven Gods, the supreme one being Tabiti. However the Scythians built places of worship to only one god: Agin, who the Greeks likened to Ares. A hereditary caste of priests who had received the gift of prophesy from the Goddess Argimpasa, used wood from willow and linden trees during their divinational rites. Horse sacrifice was incredibly common.

The Greco-Anatolian Faith is a compilation of the original greek faiths and the other semitic and phoenician dieties and faiths of Anatolia and Asia Minor. It is quite de-centralized and represents a wide-range of Greco-Anatolian beliefs and traditions.
column3:
Le monophysitisme est une hérésie apparue très tôt dans le christianisme. Contrairement au nestorianisme qui voit dans le Christ deux natures séparées, divine et humaine, les monophysites croient que le Christ possède une nature unique. Très près du miaphytisme, le monphysitisme est considéré dans le jeu comme une hérésie myaphysite. Le chef officiel de l'Église monophysite est le pape monophysite d'Alexandrie. Dans le jeu :
§Y*§!  Il y a toujours un pape d'Alexandrie, même si la cité tombe
§Y*§! Plusieurs patriarches : les cinq Pentarques et patriarches autocéphales sous le règne de rois
§Y*§! Les patriarches peuvent permettre le divorce
§Y*§! Le pape d'Alexandrie peut approuver un casus belli d'invasion
§Y*§! Les patriarches peuvent excommunier des personnages monophysites
column4:
Monophysitismus ist eine frühchristliche Häresie, die darlegt, dass Christus nur eine Natur hatte. Dies ist das Gegenstück zur Nestorianischen Position, laut der Christus zwei 'Naturen' hatte - eine göttliche und eine menschliche. Dem Miaphysitismus nahestehend, wird Monophysitismus als Miaphysitische Häresie im Spiel behandelt. Das offizielle Oberhaupt ist der Monophysitische Papst von Alexandria. Bestimmende Merkmale im Spiel: 
§Y*§! Es gibt immer einen Papst von Alexandria, selbst wenn die Stadt fällt
§Y*§! Mehrere Patriarchen - die fünf Pentarchen und autokephale Patriarchen unter Königen
§Y*§! Patriarchen können Scheidungen gewähren
§Y*§! Der Papst von Alexandria kann den Invasions-Kriegsgrund gewähren
§Y*§! Patriarchen können monophysitische Charaktere exkommunizieren
column6:
El Monofisismo es una temprana herejía Cristiana que afirma que Cristo sólo tenía una naturaleza. Esto es lo contrario a la opinión Nestoriana donde Cristo tiene dos naturalezas distintas: una divina y una humana. En estrecha relación con el Miafisismo, los Monofisistas son considerados como una herejía Miafisista dentro del juego. El jefe nominal de la Iglesia Monofisista es el Papa Monofisista de Alejandría. Definiendo características del juego:
§Y*§! Siempre hay un Papa de Alejandría, incluso si cae la ciudad
§Y*§! Múltiples  Patriarcas: los cinco Pentarcas y los Patriarcas Autocephalous por debajo de Reyes
§Y*§!  Los Patriarcas puede conceder divorcios
§Y*§! El Papa de Alejandría puede conceder la Casus Belli Invasión
§Y*§! Los Patriarcas pueden Excomulgar a personajes Monofisistas

Kiririsha is the main Goddess of the Elamites. She and her husband Humban are the highest deities in the Elamite Pantheon of gods. The Elamites revere the Goddess greatly, as she forms part of the supreme triad, which also includes Humban and Inshushinak.

column2: Unifying all of Egypt in 656 BC, The newly crowned Pharaoh Psamtik I began the Saite Dynasty and ruled Egypt until his death in 610 BC. He began his unification after the death of his father in battle against the Kushite King Tantamani and then later in 656 BC He successfully outed the last kushite-allied elements and completed the unification of the Twin Lands.

The son of the Great Assyrian King Esarhaddon, and a strong ruler in his own right, Ashurbanipal ruled the Neo-Assyrian Empire at it's height and was known as a cunning military leader and administrator. He has recently established the tributary Pharaoh Psamtik I in Egypt and vanquished the upstart Elamites under their usurper king Te-Umman. Ashurbanipal's brother, Shamash-shuma-ukin, rules in Babylonia as a vassal king and eyes his sibling's wealth and standing with envy. The Assyrian Empire is large and it's vassals and tributaries are a varied group, but history has shown that the iron discipline of Assyrian forces and a strong military leader could maintain, even expand the aging Empire.

Little is known about the faiths of the Sarmatian peoples, accounts mention the worship of a Sun god and a pantheon of several gods, similar to their Scythian neighbors. The Sarmatians seem to venerate fire and women play a strong role in their society, seemingly on equal terms with their male counterparts. Their faith does not have an organized Leadership, instead local shamans and priests lead the people in their beliefs and customs.

The faith of the early Germanic peoples since the Bronze Age, Germanic Paganism has much in common with their Neighboring Celtic beliefs, albeit being less formal and organized. Human Sacrifice is common, and elements of nature such as the Sun, Moon, and Fire are held in religious esteem. Divination and Augury were common, but without an official Druidic class to preside over it, the traditions and local gods varied from village to village. In-game the faith is titled Tuistic after the prominent figure from Germanic Mythology.

The Etruscans believed that all of visible creation was the manifestation of divine power. Their pantheon was lead by the trio of Tinia, Uni, and Cel. Menrva later replaced Cel under Greek influence. A highly organised caste of priests led the population through worship by using haruspicy, the inspection of dissected animal organs.

Often rewarded only to the most loyal or distinguished subjects, the position of Varušânhâ was considered highly honoured as it symbolized a close relationship between the holder and the Achaemenid Royal family.

The Free citizens of this city train here in preparation for war and to defend their homes. Hoplites are well-armoured and equipped and are reliable soldiers in battle. They form the bulk of the standing armies of most greek forces.
the citizenry of this city train here in the greek fashion of hoplons and spears and drill to fight in a phalanx formation.

The Somatophylakes were the chosen bodyguards of Phillip II and Alexander the Great, being especially chosen for their personal loyalty and martial ability in battle.

Playing as a member of the nobility within a Mesopotamian Government is not entirely dissimilar to a Nobility-based Government - although the concentration of power is the hands of the ruler and his or her upper court, with lower vassals and nobility being at the mercy of a strong central government. The centralization and traditions of this form of government allow for a larger amount of vassal subjects.

The Vedic-influenced monarch-based system of governance in ancient india was primarily male-centric and saw local lords and kings form absolute monarchies over their subjects. The Indian equivalent of a feudal system of Governance but with less restraints placed upon the lord or king while allowing for religious differences to foster between their subjects.
A feat of Mesopotamian architectural design and administrative capability, this sprawling structure houses scholars and viceroys who toil in earnest to see society led properly.

column2: Lusitanian deities heavily influenced all of the religious practices in western Iberia, namely also in Gallaecia. They mingled with Roman deities after Lusitania was conquered. Of particular importance and popularity were a number of deities among whom the most important was Endovelicus (god of healing). Other gods of the pantheon include Nabia (goddess of water) and Trebaruna (goddess of home and families).

There is much speculation concerning the religion based around Zalmoxis, a Thracian God-turned-human prohet and (possibly) back again into a God-like form. The religion was exclusive to the more northerly Daco-Thracian peoples such as the Getae and the Dacians. By the time of Trajan's conquest in 860 AUC, Zalmoxism was a very organised state religion based around the king.

Not much is known of the structure of the southern Thracian religion, but it is likely that it wasn't as centralised as other religions of the era due to the lack of a central religious authority or state. The most prominent God across the region however seems to be Sabazios who was often portrayed as a horseman bearing a staff entwined with a snake. There was a pantheon of other Gods, but most evidence points to Sabazios being considered a major deity of sorts.

The Celtic religion covered an immense area in Europe, yet surprisingly there was a degree of orthodoxy. The druid class were second in society only to the nobility and were intermediaries between humans and the Gods. Furthermore, the Celts believed that the Gods and spirits were present in all natural beings and because of this there was a reverance for nature.

column2: A form of Zoroastrianism in which the divinity Zurvan engenders both Ahura Mazda and Angra Mainyu. Zurvan is perceived as a neutral and transcendental god for whom there is no distinction of good and evil. Zurvanism is viewed as a sacerdotal response to resolve a perceived inconsistency in the sacred texts of Zoroastrianism. This heresy has no religious head and no special game mechanics.
Once every 20 years, you may issue orders to arrest those who follow a different faith than you. This order targets officials in your realm and sends out soldiers with orders to arrest them.

The Greeks guarded their independence closely and as a result the polis or city, instead of the state, became the central identity in Ancient Greece. Due to their internal focus, and the independant nature of local people, the Greek model of governance places severe limits on having numerous vassals and ruling more than one city-state. It is not impossible, just difficult.

column2: Little is known of the structure of the Illyrian religion, but it can be surmised that it was very decentralised due to the fractious nature of the Illyrian tribes. It is also probable that the religion was generally similar to the Daco-Thracian religions. Local Gods predominated among the tribe, yet didn't seem to spread their influence further.

'Greco-Italic' is the term used to refer to the religion practiced by the Italic peoples who were significantly influenced by Greek and Etruscan religious beliefs. In-game it isn't called 'Roman' because of the possibility of Rome's early demise.
